Taiwan Stocks: Acer, AU Optronics, First Financial, Hon Hai

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-12-01T06:00:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-01/taiwan-stock-movers-acer-au-optronics-first-financial-holding.html
Shares of the following companies had
 unusual (TWSE)  moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are at the close in Taipei.  The Taiex Index gained 4 percent to 7,178.69, the largest
advance since May 4, 2009.  Acer Inc. (2353)  (2353 TT), the world’s fourth-largest computer
maker, jumped 4.8 percent to NT$35.10, the highest close since
Nov. 17. The company will return to profit this quarter as it no
longer has the excess inventory problems that led to losses in
the previous two periods, President Jim Wong said yesterday.  AU Optronics Corp. (2409)  (2409 TT) surged 6.8 percent to NT$15,
the highest close since Nov. 15. Yawen Hsiao, a spokeswoman for
the company, confirmed an Economic Daily News report that cited
Chairman K.Y. Lee as saying flat-panel prices increased on a
rush of orders following Black Friday holiday sales.  First Financial Holding Co. (2892)  (2892 TT) advanced 7 percent to
NT$18.40, the biggest jump since Oct. 30, 2008. First Securities
Inc. plan to sign a cooperation agreement with China’s Century
Securities Co. after getting regulatory approval, parent First
Financial said in a statement to the Taiwan stock exchange.  Hon Hai Precision Industry Co. (2317)  (2317 TT) increased 3.9
percent to NT$82.80, the steepest gain since Nov. 11. Parent
Foxconn Technology Group, the world’s largest contract maker of
electronics, will post revenue growth of at least 15 percent
next year, Chairman Terry Gou said today in Kaohsiung, southern
Taiwan. Gou last year cut his annual growth target to 15 percent
from a 30 percent rate in place for more than a decade.  To contact the reporter on this story:
